  "prompt": "How much does an Olympic gold medal cost?",
  "response": "The monetary cost of an Olympic gold medal can vary depending on the materials and craftsmanship involved, but it is worth noting that the medals are not pure gold. According to the International Olympic Committee (IOC), gold medals must be made of at least 92.5% silver and plated with at least 6 grams of gold. The actual value of the materials in an Olympic gold medal is relatively modest.\n\nAs of recent estimates (e.g., the Tokyo 2020 Olympics), the raw materials in a gold medal are worth approximately $800 to $1,000 USD. The silver content makes up the bulk of the value, while the gold plating adds a smaller portion.\n\nHowever, the intrinsic value of an Olympic gold medal pales in comparison to its symbolic and historical significance. For athletes, the medal represents years of dedication, hard work, and achievement, making it priceless in that context. Additionally, medals from historic or iconic Games can fetch significant sums if sold at auction, often reaching hundreds of thousands or even millions of dollars.",
